  "why": "The paper focuses on the efficient generation and validation of failures in Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) systems using a black-box, differential testing approach. It successfully reports thousands of validated failures and provides high-level statistics, such as which ASR system fails most often. However, it does not provide diagnostic analysis into the root causes of these failures. The main analysis section (IV-B) is dedicated to diagnosing the false positives of the proposed CrossASR method itself, attributing them to issues with the Text-To-Speech (TTS) engine, text preprocessing, or ambiguous audio. This analysis explains the limitations of the testing framework but does not investigate why the ASR models genuinely fail on the true positive test cases. The paper presents examples of failures but does not connect them to underlying model vulnerabilities like dataset bias or reliance on spurious features.",
